在'''[[印度尼西亚|印度尼西亚]]'''，'''女[[同性戀|同性戀]]、男同性恋、双性恋和跨性别（[[LGBT|LGBT]]）'''人群面临着非[[LGBT|LGBT]]居民没有经历过的法律挑战和偏见。传统习俗不赞成同性婚姻和[[異裝|異裝]]，也影响了公共政策的制定。例如，印度尼西亚同性伴侣和以同性伴侣为户主的家庭没有资格获得[[异性恋|异性]]婚姻夫妇可获得的任何法律保护。印度尼西亚没有俗稱[[雞姦法|雞姦法]]的反同性性行為歧視法律，目前也没有将成年人之间自愿的非商业性的私人同性性行为定为刑事犯罪，但印度尼西亚法律也并不保护LGBT社区免遭[[歧视|歧视]]和[[仇恨犯罪|仇恨犯罪]]。目前，印度尼西亚不承认[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]。2015年7月，印度尼西亚宗教事务部长表示，在印度尼西亚同性恋是不被接受的，因为宗教规范强烈反对这种行为。<ref name="JP Gay Marriage">{{cite news | title = Difficult for Indonesia to legalize gay marriage: Minister | location = Jakarta | date = 2015-07-02 | newspaper = The Jakarta Post | url = http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/07/02/difficult-indonesia-legalize-gay-marriage-minister.html | accessdate = 2016-11-02 | archive-date = 2018-11-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181117073932/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/07/02/difficult-indonesia-legalize-gay-marriage-minister.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>印度尼西亚强调社会和谐的重要性，注重义务而不是权利，这意味着人权与LGBT权利一样非常脆弱。<ref name=Offord>{{Cite journal
  | last = Offord
  | first = Baden
  |author2=Cantrell, Leon
   | title = Homosexual Rights as Human Rights in Indonesia and Australia
  | journal = Journal of Homosexuality
  | volume = 40
  | issue = 3&4
  | pages = 233–252
  | publisher = Routledge
  | location =
  | date = May 2001
  | issn = 0091-8369
  | doi = 10.1300/J082v40n03_12
  | id =}}</ref>然而，印度尼西亚的LGBT社区正在稳步地变得更有能见度政治上也更活跃。<ref name=Offord/>

最近，印度尼西亚的LGBT人群正面临越来越大的敌意。<ref name="NYT-1">{{cite news | title = Anti-Gay Actions in Indonesia Threaten a Fragile Population | author = Jeffrey Hutton | date = 2016-02-15 | newspaper = The New York Times | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/16/world/asia/indonesia-antigay-sentiment.html?_r=0 | accessdate = 2016-11-02 | archive-date = 2021-02-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210224195946/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/16/world/asia/indonesia-antigay-sentiment.html?_r=0 | dead-url = no }}</ref>2016年初，印度尼西亚的LGBT人群和活动家面临着更激烈的反对、[[恐同|恐同]]袭击和[[仇恨言论|仇恨言论]]，甚至有些是由印度尼西亚当局发起。<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news | work = Reuters | date = 2016-03-08 | title = Under attack, Indonesian LGBT groups set up safehouses, live in fear | author = Alisa Tang | url = http://www.reuters.com/article/us-indonesia-gay-rights-idUSKCN0WB02Z | accessdate = 2016-11-02 | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108112849/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-indonesia-gay-rights-idUSKCN0WB02Z | dead-url = no }}</ref>2016年2月，[[人权观察|人权观察]]敦促印度尼西亚政府捍卫LGBT群体的权利并公开谴责官员的歧视言论。<ref name="HRW-1">{{cite web | date = 2016-02-11 | title = Indonesia: Flurry of Anti-Gay Statements by Officials, Condemn Bias; Pledge to Protect LGBT Groups | work = Human Rights Watch | url = https://www.hrw.org/news/2016/02/11/indonesia-flurry-anti-gay-statements-officials | accessdate = 2016-11-02 | archive-date = 2019-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190125212804/https://www.hrw.org/news/2016/02/11/indonesia-flurry-anti-gay-statements-officials | dead-url = no }}</ref>

由于害怕社会的拒绝和不良影响，印度尼西亚的LGBT人士很少向家人和朋友[[出柜|出柜]]。但也有部分的家庭了解和接受LGBT人群。<ref name="LGBT-JP1">{{cite news | title = A portrait of a gay Indonesian | author = Liza Yosephine | newspaper = The Jakarta Post | url = http://www.thejakartapost.com/longform/2016/05/16/a-portrait-of-a-gay-indonesian.html | accessdate = 2016-11-02 | archive-date = 2018-11-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181103054403/http://www.thejakartapost.com/longform/2016/05/16/a-portrait-of-a-gay-indonesian.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

2020年2月，《[[雅加達郵報|雅加達郵報]]》報導，5名[[印度尼西亞共和國人民代表會議|印尼人民代表會議]]議員提出《健全家庭法草案》，將LGBT群體定義為[[性偏差|性偏差]]的[[社會對同性戀的態度|社會認同]]問題，要求其家庭成員舉報至相關機構並強制矯正。<ref>{{Cite web|title=印尼擬定義LGBT性偏差 考慮立法強制矯正|url=https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/202002190394.aspx|author=石秀娟|date=2020-02-20|accessdate=2020-02-22|work=中央通訊社|language=zh-tw|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928015906/https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/202002190394.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Bedroom bill: Proposed ‘family resilience’ law would require LGBT people to report for ‘rehabilitation’|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/19/bedroom-bill-proposed-family-resilience-law-would-require-lgbt-people-to-report-for-rehabilitation.html|date=2020-02-19|accessdate=2020-02-22|author=Budi Sutrisno|work=The Jakarta Post|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202020241/https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/19/bedroom-bill-proposed-family-resilience-law-would-require-lgbt-people-to-report-for-rehabilitation.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

